<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id90974ecb-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s5724"><num value="5724">§ 5724.</num><heading> Consultation with Congress</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In carrying out this subchapter, the President shall consult appropriately with the Congress.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id90974ecc-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/102/383/tII/s204">Pub. L. 102–383, title II, § 204</ref>, <date date="1992-10-05">Oct. 5, 1992</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/106/1453">106 Stat. 1453</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
